content:
You can loop through an array by pairs and then do a nested loop inside the pair. For example create a table with two columns:<pre>&lt;table&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<% @names.each_slice(2) do |slice| -%>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;tr&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<% slice.each do |name| -%>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;td&gt;<%= name %>&lt;/td&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<% end -%>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/tr&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<% end -%>
&lt;/table&gt;</pre>
